    <note type="biography">
        <p>Physician and ethnologist. MD, Edinburgh, 1808. Studied at Trinity College, Cambridge, and St John’s and Trinity Colleges, Oxford. Physician, Bristol Infirmary, until 1843. In <hi rend="italic">Researches into the physical history of man</hi> (1813), maintained that human races were varieties of one species. A commissioner of lunacy in London, 1845. FRS 1827.</p></note>
